# Swarm runtime

## Entry point

All multi-agent work starts with **Commander attach** — read `skills/swarm-runtime/SKILL.md` and `.among-check/hub.toon` before delegating to scouts.

## Isolation

- One **Sandbox** per Git repository
- Scouts work in **Anchors** (git worktrees), not directly on `main`
- Tasks live in **Markers** (`markers/`) — git is the source of truth

## Workflow

1. Read `markers/index.toon` + `audits/latest.toon`
2. Assign **Sweeps** (batched markers) to one scout each
3. Persist progress in anchor `state.toon`
4. Complete via **Gate** (test + re-scan) when `gateRequired: true`

## Parallel sessions

Recommend **tmux** for multiple scouts and Silver sentinel patrol.

See `docs/swarm-runtime.md` and `docs/architecture.md` §16.
